            "text": "I have executed the startup benchmark with 30 successful samples. Below is the summary of the measured latency metrics for the sandbox lifecycle:\n\n### Warm-Instance Sandbox Startup Metrics (30 Samples)\n\n*   **Minimum:** 408.94 ms\n*   **p50 (Median):** 428.35 ms\n*   **Mean:** 431.90 ms\n*   **p95:** 455.85 ms\n*   **p99:** 470.93 ms\n*   **Maximum:** 470.93 ms\n\n### Important Distinction regarding Latency Metrics\nPlease note that these metrics specifically measure the one-shot creation, execution of a trivial command (`/bin/true`), and immediate deletion of the egress-denied container sandbox **within an already warm, running Cloud Run instance**. \n\nThis latency **does not** include:\n1.  **Cloud Run service cold starts** (the time it takes for Google Cloud to provision a new container instance for the hosting service itself).\n2.  **Model generation/reasoning latency** (the time the LLM takes to process, think, and generate the response).\n3.  **Network Round-Trip Time (RTT)** between your client, the LLM provider, and the underlying cloud infrastructure.",
